positionAlongCurve

public boolean positionAlongCurve(Curve3D c,
                                  float time)
Set the position of this NeuronMorphology at point time along curve c, or does nothing if it is a free-floating neuron

Parameters:
c - The curve to position this neuron along
time - The time to place it along the curve from [0,1]
Returns:
True if moved successfully, returns false if it does not move (free-floating neurons)

getCable

public NeuronCable getCable(int i)
Retrieves the cable at position i. IMPORTANT NOTE: This method does not return a new reference each time it is called. Instead it uses the same instance of a cable each time and simply calls a set method to make it into the appropriate cable. Do not add these cables to any collections or they will not work correctly.
